Defendant is Alan Ray Rifkin.

17:49.068 --> 17:52.526
Not here. I don't want
the people | work with
knowing I'm involved in this.

17:52.697 --> 17:56.189
I'm running out of time, Mr. Munson.
Alan Ray Rifkin is running out of time.

17:56.367 --> 17:59.359
I know that. Why the hell
do you think I came fonNard?

17:59.579 --> 18:01.490
Came fonNard? To whom?

18:03.040 --> 18:06.123
That group, the one that fights
against the death penalty.

18:06.294 --> 18:07.875
The Amnesty Collective.

18:08.087 --> 18:10.703
You and Cooper, you were
at Andrews when Rifkin landed.

18:10.881 --> 18:12.792
You drove him.
Yeah, I was there.

18:13.009 --> 18:15.421
But Cooper and me,
we weren't the only ones.

18:15.595 --> 18:18.337
That prosecutor, Tom Connally,
he was waiting on the tarmac.

18:18.514 --> 18:20.630
Connally was there?
Yeah. He was angry.

18:20.808 --> 18:22.799
Said the Rifkin case
was assigned to him.

18:22.977 --> 18:25.434
Kept saying they
didn't have enough to convict.

18:25.605 --> 18:27.061
He was going places,
you know.

18:27.273 --> 18:30.731
And he wasn't gonna wreck his career
by losing a high-profile case.

18:30.901 --> 18:33.438
You heard this?
He said they needed a confession.

18:33.613 --> 18:36.571
He told Cooper to pick him up,
take him to one of the hangars

18:36.741 --> 18:38.732
and not let him out
until he admitted it.

18:39.493 --> 18:40.653
[m1

18:40.828 --> 18:44.912
Mr. Munson, did Agent Cooper
physically coerce Rifkin?

18:45.750 --> 18:47.581
Physically coerce?

18:47.752 --> 18:49.993
Man, you feds are too much.

18:50.212 --> 18:51.543
He beat him, yeah.

18:52.340 --> 18:55.082
I swapped out the entry log,
made the timeline make sense

18:55.259 --> 18:58.342
and I had Rifkin treated in his cell
instead of the infirmary

18:58.512 --> 19:00.673
to avoid any record.

19:00.890 --> 19:03.506
Everyone said
he was betraying our country,

19:04.310 --> 19:06.847
but now if he's really gonna die...

19:09.982 --> 19:11.973
[SIGHS]

19:16.530 --> 19:18.145
COOPER:
Tom.

19:18.366 --> 19:20.231
Harold. What are you
doing out this way?

19:20.409 --> 19:22.616
Looking for you, Tom.

19:22.828 --> 19:25.240
We have a problem with Rifkin.

19:25.790 --> 19:27.951
We need to contain this.

19:36.050 --> 19:38.086
[m1

19:45.226 --> 19:46.591
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

20:00.533 --> 20:03.650
I found a flash drive,
and your girl.

20:03.869 --> 20:05.245
I got some stuff.

20:05.788 --> 20:09.246
The last six months she’s been
in Havana, Port-au-Prince, Miami.

20:10.126 --> 20:11.662
Various aliases.

20:11.836 --> 20:13.372
Last September she was in Prague.

20:13.546 --> 20:16.288
Miss Jolene is definitely moving
toward something.

20:16.465 --> 20:19.252
Red, best I can tell,
girl's tracking someone.

20:19.427 --> 20:20.712
Causing trouble.

20:20.886 --> 20:25.926
She's either got lots of little targets
or one real big one.

20:30.062 --> 20:32.053
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

20:33.816 --> 20:37.729
We need to talk about Rifkin.
I've said everything I have to say.

20:37.903 --> 20:40.155
Sir, I need to know
whether you...

20:42.450 --> 20:44.406
What's going on?

20:44.702 --> 20:46.988
Agent Keen, this is
US. Attorney Tom Connally.

20:47.163 --> 20:50.496
Harold's been telling me
what a great agent you are.

20:50.708 --> 20:52.448
Dog with a bone.

20:54.754 --> 20:56.335
Sir, may we speak privately?

20:56.505 --> 21:00.089
The thing is, this Rifkin case,
the court has made its decision.

21:00.259 --> 21:03.797
Agent Keen, whatever you
have to say to me, you can
say to both of us.

21:05.973 --> 21:09.386
I need to know what happened at
the airport after you landed with Rifkin.

21:10.019 --> 21:12.226
Rifkin was transferred
to a holding facility.

21:12.396 --> 21:14.227
You beat a confession out of him.

21:14.398 --> 21:16.810
Who told you that?
Your transport log was doctored.

21:16.984 --> 21:19.976
This is the real log, which shows
how long he was at the airport.

21:20.154 --> 21:21.189
There's a two-hour gap.

21:21.363 --> 21:23.979
Where'd you get that?
Does it matter?

21:24.158 --> 21:27.025
Let's not play games.
You clearly have a theory,
let's hear it.

21:27.203 --> 21:28.409
I don't have a theory.

21:28.579 --> 21:30.820
l have a witness who says
he heard you

21:30.998 --> 21:33.239
order you to beat a confession
out of Rifkin.

21:33.417 --> 21:36.955
He saw it happen.
I did not railroad an innocent man.

21:37.171 --> 21:40.004
There were witnesses.
Firsthand accounts.

21:41.342 --> 21:42.752
Did you beat him?

21:42.968 --> 21:44.754
[m1

21:44.929 --> 21:46.590
Yes.

21:46.764 --> 21:51.258
Agent Keen, Alan Ray Rifkin deserves
the sentence he received for his crimes.

21:51.435 --> 21:53.175
He's being transferred for execution.

21:53.354 --> 21:56.061
We have to stop it until
the court looks at his confession.

21:56.232 --> 21:58.723
His day in court is over.
He's exhausted his appeals.

21:58.901 --> 22:01.438
Once that happens,
the Supreme Court is clear.

22:01.612 --> 22:04.649
Why he confessed or whether
he's even guilty becomes irrelevant.

22:04.824 --> 22:07.486
We'll see if the federal clemency
officer agrees with you.

22:07.660 --> 22:10.652
Heh. He won't even agree
to a meeting.

22:11.288 --> 22:14.621
Be careful who you go around
talking to, Agent Keen.

22:17.127 --> 22:19.163
Are you telling me this or is he?

22:20.548 --> 22:23.961
The only career you should
worry about is your own.

22:32.434 --> 22:34.470
FEDERAL WARDEN:
Upon arrival at the execution facility,

22:34.645 --> 22:38.479
the condemned shall be provided
a Form BP—199

22:38.649 --> 22:41.766
in which he will be asked
where his body is to be sent.

22:41.944 --> 22:45.277
I understand. No, he's
the federal clemency officer.

22:45.447 --> 22:46.732
I need to talk to him.

22:47.283 --> 22:48.944
Yes, please have him call me.

22:49.118 --> 22:51.905
FEDERAL WARDEN:
He may have not more than
one spiritual advisor,

22:52.079 --> 22:55.537
two defense attorneys
and up to ﬁve adult friends or relatives.

22:55.708 --> 22:58.825
Connally was right. They don't consider
the event logs new evidence.

22:59.003 --> 23:00.413
And even if they did,

23:00.588 --> 23:04.080
the deadline to consider Rifkin's
factual innocence has passed.

23:04.675 --> 23:06.757
Do they realize how insane that is?

23:06.927 --> 23:09.259
His innocence can't be considered?

23:09.471 --> 23:11.632
[m1

23:13.893 --> 23:15.099
[GRUNTING]

23:28.407 --> 23:30.523
RIFKIN:
ljust wanna say...

23:31.535 --> 23:32.775
I didn't do it.

23:33.996 --> 23:37.409
You're killing an innocent man
here tonight.

23:40.628 --> 23:42.960
Even God won't forgive you
for this.

23:43.547 --> 23:45.083
[m1

23:46.175 --> 23:47.415
We're ready.

23:52.806 --> 23:54.717
Good night, Mother.

23:57.269 --> 23:59.510
Good night. Good night.

24:11.158 --> 24:12.568
[FLATLINING]

24:20.125 --> 24:24.539
We did the right thing.
Yes, just not the right way.

24:24.713 --> 24:29.503
Let me ask you something.
That agent, Keen, the task force...

24:29.677 --> 24:32.259
I mean, I've asked around
on the hill, main justice,

24:32.805 --> 24:35.672
nobody knows
what the hell it is you do.

24:35.849 --> 24:37.305
I've heard the stories.

24:37.518 --> 24:39.634
They say you guys
are taking down everybody.

24:39.853 --> 24:43.186
People who aren't even
on our radar. How?

24:43.357 --> 24:46.520
Ha, ha. Nothing? Really?
Ha, ha.

24:47.277 --> 24:49.063
Well, I can tell you this.

24:49.238 --> 24:51.103
When I'm attorney general

24:51.281 --> 24:54.239
and | get the president
to appoint you director of the FBI,

24:55.202 --> 24:59.741
you're gonna tell me all about it,
the truth about your secret weapon.

25:00.124 --> 25:01.830
Because we both know you have one.

25:02.001 --> 25:05.835
[m1

25:20.769 --> 25:21.804
[FRANK SHOUTS
INDISTINCTLY]

25:21.979 --> 25:23.515
Don't move.
Ow. Aah.

25:29.945 --> 25:31.936
[m1

25:38.537 --> 25:40.323
The Judge would like to see you.

25:43.834 --> 25:47.998
An innocent man is dead
because of you.

25:48.672 --> 25:51.209
Because you lied.
Alan Ray Rifkin was a terrorist.

25:51.383 --> 25:53.089
You beat him.

25:53.719 --> 25:56.085
You forced a confession.
To a crime he committed.

26:03.520 --> 26:05.806
[m1

26:05.981 --> 26:07.972
Cooper's been taken.
By whom?

26:08.150 --> 26:11.642
The Judge, we think.
As retribution for Rifkin's execution.

26:12.112 --> 26:13.192
Anything?
Not yet.

26:13.363 --> 26:15.194
Alan Ray Rifkin?
We've got nothing.

26:15.365 --> 26:17.276
No license plate,
no surveillance footage.

26:17.451 --> 26:20.284
They could be anywhere by now.
Back up, Lizzy. Rifkin.

26:20.454 --> 26:22.365
Go back to Rifkin.

26:22.539 --> 26:26.077
Why would the Judge hold Cooper
responsible for his execution?

26:26.251 --> 26:28.287
Because he coerced
Rifkin's confession.

26:28.462 --> 26:31.078
You're certain of that?
Cooper admitted it to me.

26:31.256 --> 26:33.838
How about the guy the Judge
released, Hastings?

26:34.009 --> 26:37.342
We're getting a court order to talk
to him over his doctor's objections.

26:37.513 --> 26:40.926
He's worried about further trauma.
If you ever wanna see Cooper again,

26:41.100 --> 26:42.886
you need to get Hastings to talk.

26:43.268 --> 26:46.055
Lizzy, [must be going.
Wait. Did you hear me?

26:46.230 --> 26:50.064
Rifkin was executed. An eye
for an eye. Cooper is going to die.

26:50.234 --> 26:52.225
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

26:52.903 --> 26:56.862
Dembe, you better tell Edward
there's gonna be a change in flight plan.

26:57.324 --> 27:00.487
KlPLlNG:
A woman's son is dead
because of you.

27:00.661 --> 27:05.746
A husband, father, brother.

27:06.750 --> 27:07.990
A good man.

27:08.168 --> 27:10.830
Rifkin was given every opportunity
to prove his innocence.

27:12.005 --> 27:14.872
Prove to who? To you?

27:15.342 --> 27:18.254
To the very people who
framed him in the first place?

27:18.804 --> 27:21.921
You know, if you
did yourjob right,

27:22.099 --> 27:25.591
I wouldn't have to do mine!

27:26.145 --> 27:27.885
[m1

27:31.150 --> 27:35.314
How do you plead?
Lady, this thing you're doing, this--

27:35.487 --> 27:39.400
This is a horrible mistake.
I said, how do you plead?

27:39.575 --> 27:43.989
I guess I plead not guilty.

27:56.800 --> 27:58.540
Madam.

27:59.178 --> 28:00.918
| find you guilty.

28:01.096 --> 28:03.087
[BANGING ON PRISON BARS]

28:16.195 --> 28:17.651
[SIGHS]

28:17.821 --> 28:19.322
RAYMOND:
Richard.

28:21.491 --> 28:23.903
Say something, Richard.

28:27.039 --> 28:30.531
I keep meaning to attend
our academy class reunions.

28:30.709 --> 28:34.418
Then I remember how pinched
I look in Dinner Dress Blues.

28:34.588 --> 28:36.704
What the hell do you want?

28:36.924 --> 28:39.836
How's your family?
My wife left me, thanks.

28:40.052 --> 28:44.546
After I was sidelined. You made
a hell of a mess when you left.

28:44.723 --> 28:46.679
Nobody believed
we couldn't see it coming.

28:46.850 --> 28:48.010
Maybe we helped you,

28:48.185 --> 28:51.018
maybe we facilitated
your treason.

28:51.188 --> 28:55.431
Even without any evidence,
it was enough to destroy
some careers.

28:56.026 --> 28:57.232
Yes.

28:58.612 --> 29:01.695
Richard, I need to know
about the Rifkin case.

29:01.907 --> 29:04.489
He claimed civilians
were fired on by soldiers

29:04.660 --> 29:07.572
from a Black Hawk that
CENTCOM says it never deployed.

29:07.746 --> 29:09.953
I can't help you.

29:10.707 --> 29:14.120
You were operational
in the Guldara District.

29:14.336 --> 29:18.170
If there were choppers in the air,
you knew about it.

29:18.632 --> 29:21.544
Rooming with you was
the worst thing that ever
happened to me.

29:22.678 --> 29:25.795
I'm offering you an opportunity,
Richard.

29:26.014 --> 29:29.472
The men who want
this information can be...

29:30.102 --> 29:31.137
very helpful.

29:32.813 --> 29:36.897
If you help them,
it could put you back on track.

29:37.526 --> 29:38.936
LIZ:
I'm so sorry, Mr. Hastings.

29:39.111 --> 29:42.478
I can't imagine how difficult
this must be for you.

29:42.948 --> 29:47.567
But there are others,
still there, being held.

29:48.036 --> 29:50.152
I need to know where you were held.
DONNA: Enough.

29:50.998 --> 29:53.865
Please. Just go.

30:00.924 --> 30:02.835
Good night, Mother.

30:03.051 --> 30:06.214
No, Mark. It's me.
It's Donna.

30:06.388 --> 30:08.379
[m1

30:08.765 --> 30:09.800
LIZ:
Aram.

30:09.975 --> 30:13.638
The papers said Rifkin's
last words at his execution were,
"Good night, Mother."

30:13.812 --> 30:16.098
He said it to his spiritual advisor,
Ruth Kipling.

30:16.273 --> 30:18.355
| just heard Hastings say it.

30:19.860 --> 30:23.978
ARAM:
Okay, Ruth Suzanne Kipling. Single,
62. Attended Vassar College

30:24.156 --> 30:27.648
and co-founded the prison-rights
organization, the Amnesty Collective.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.317
The marshal that covered up
for Cooper and Connally,

30:30.495 --> 30:32.531
that's the organization
he reached out to.

30:32.706 --> 30:35.664
Which is how Kipling found out
about the entry-log evidence.

30:35.959 --> 30:38.291
I've got an address in
Mercer County, Pennsylvania.

30:38.462 --> 30:40.123
LIZ:
Bet that's where she's holding them.

30:40.297 --> 30:42.288
[BANGING ON PRISON BARS]

30:45.510 --> 30:47.375
[m1

30:55.604 --> 30:57.686
We ready, Frank?

31:01.109 --> 31:03.065
[GENERATOR WHIRRING]

31:19.836 --> 31:21.827
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]

31:22.005 --> 31:23.916
[m1

31:26.009 --> 31:27.340
LlZ [OVER PHONE]: Red.
Lizzy.

31:27.719 --> 31:30.301
Have you located Harold?
Yes, we're almost there.

31:30.472 --> 31:32.508
There's been a development.

31:32.724 --> 31:34.715
[m1

31:40.524 --> 31:44.608
KlPLlNG:
Thus do I commend thee
into the arms of our Lord Jesus Christ,

31:44.820 --> 31:50.156
the preserver of all mercy
and reality, and the Father--

31:50.325 --> 31:51.610
We got a problem.

32:00.252 --> 32:03.289
RESSLER:
Captain, I need you to get your men
out of here. Fall back, now.

32:03.463 --> 32:04.999
Move, move, let's go.

32:05.382 --> 32:08.920
What are they doing?
Why are they moving back?

32:10.971 --> 32:12.962
They wanna talk.

32:14.850 --> 32:18.763
Ruth, this is not a tactic.
I'm not trying to negotiate.

32:19.521 --> 32:21.853
Yes, new information
on the Rifkin case.

32:22.023 --> 32:25.356
Someone with high-level access
is en route.

32:25.527 --> 32:26.642
[m1

32:26.862 --> 32:29.194
[BANGING ON PRISON BARS]

32:45.046 --> 32:47.037
ﬁAUGHS]

32:47.340 --> 32:49.126
Of course...

32:49.885 --> 32:51.250
a woman.

32:52.220 --> 32:54.677
If you came to advocate
on behalf of Agent Cooper--

32:54.848 --> 32:56.008
I didn't.

32:57.559 --> 32:58.719
I came to advocate

32:58.894 --> 33:00.976
on behalf of you.

33:01.480 --> 33:05.189
After devoting your life
to a pursuit of the truth

33:05.358 --> 33:07.735
to making things right,

33:08.195 --> 33:13.064
it would be such a shame
in your last act to get it so wrong.

33:14.159 --> 33:18.698
This is a classified Pentagon file
on the Rifkin case.

33:18.914 --> 33:20.779
In the spirit of full disclosure,

33:20.957 --> 33:24.245
it's a felony for me to have it
or for you to see it.

33:24.419 --> 33:27.957
But under the circumstances,
who are we to quibble?

33:29.633 --> 33:35.799
It states that on October 3rd, 2002,
US. military intelligence officers

33:35.972 --> 33:39.806
deployed a unit by helicopter
to the village of Guldara

33:40.310 --> 33:42.471
in the Kabul Province
of Afghanistan

33:42.646 --> 33:47.140
to extract an asset whose identity
had been compromised.

33:47.317 --> 33:53.108
The Taliban in the area, with whom
Alan Ray Rifkin had aligned himself,

33:53.323 --> 33:56.656
got word of the informant
and advanced on the village.

33:56.868 --> 33:58.779
But they were too late.

33:58.995 --> 34:02.658
The boys had extracted
their asset and left.

34:03.333 --> 34:05.699
Angry and suspicious of others,

34:05.877 --> 34:10.166
the Taliban and Rifkin set fire
to the village and executed inhabitants.

34:10.840 --> 34:15.550
Dozens of women and children
were killed at the hands of the Taliban

34:15.720 --> 34:20.214
in response to US.
military intelligence in the area.

34:20.392 --> 34:22.678
I guess fearing more headlines,

34:22.852 --> 34:26.310
the Pentagon wanted
no association with the incident

34:26.481 --> 34:28.688
so they covered it up.

34:29.067 --> 34:31.308
That is what happened.

34:32.320 --> 34:33.696
That is the truth.

34:34.864 --> 34:39.608
That's why you're not gonna
light up Agent Cooper today.

34:39.828 --> 34:44.117
Alan Ray Rifkin wasn't executed
because of a beating

34:44.332 --> 34:46.664
or because of a cover-up.

34:47.168 --> 34:50.001
He was executed because of
the truth.

34:50.171 --> 34:55.040
Now, you and I could talk for days about
the why's and why not's of an execution,

34:55.218 --> 34:58.961
but at the end of it all,
in the final moment,

34:59.180 --> 35:05.267
the only irrefutable fact is,
you better be right.

35:06.021 --> 35:08.933
And I'm betting
you're not so sure.

35:10.442 --> 35:12.854
How could you possibly know
what I'm thinking?

35:14.696 --> 35:16.402
Mark Hastings.

35:17.824 --> 35:19.485
You let him go...

35:20.327 --> 35:23.114
because he'd served his time.

35:23.955 --> 35:30.167
Because this has always been about
justice in your eyes, not blind revenge.

35:30.378 --> 35:35.042
The day you started this,
you knew it would inevitably end.

35:35.216 --> 35:39.505
That when you released your
first prisoner, you would get caught.

35:40.096 --> 35:45.511
You don't wanna diminish your legacy
of righteousness because of him.

35:47.437 --> 35:49.678
Which is why
you're going to surrender.

35:55.111 --> 35:58.603
Harold, don't look so glum.

36:16.091 --> 36:18.082
[m1

36:32.232 --> 36:35.269
MAN 1: Come on, sir.
MAN 2: Get a medical attention outfit.

36:38.905 --> 36:41.191
MAN 3:
Hey, it's all right.

36:43.660 --> 36:46.618
I thought you were gone.
What happened?

36:46.830 --> 36:48.912
My secret weapon.

36:53.503 --> 36:57.166
COOPER:
Five prosecutors,
a federal judge, two cops.

36:57.340 --> 36:59.797
There were 10 people in that bunker.

37:00.927 --> 37:02.133
What's this?

37:02.303 --> 37:06.467
Pleas we found in
Frank Gordon's room from
prisoners all over the country.

37:07.726 --> 37:10.138
Send it to the
Justice Department for review.

37:10.311 --> 37:11.972
Walk with me?

37:13.273 --> 37:15.059
Agent Keen,

37:15.316 --> 37:19.605
I regret the methods that
we employed to obtain
Rifkin's confession.

37:19.821 --> 37:23.188
If you feel obligated to report it,
I understand.

37:23.867 --> 37:26.609
I think we've had enough judgment
for today.

37:29.164 --> 37:33.032
You knew this was gonna happen,
with me, the Judge.

37:33.251 --> 37:36.835
If you thought that by saving me
you'd get some kind of leverage--

37:37.005 --> 37:40.668
Harold, a war is coming.

37:41.551 --> 37:45.965
I believe the incursion at this facility
and the rather sudden disappearance

37:46.139 --> 37:48.346
of Diane Fowler
were just the beginning.

37:48.558 --> 37:51.721
And I'm certain things will get
considerably worse

37:51.936 --> 37:53.892
before they get better.

37:57.901 --> 38:00.358
You want my help.
Not now.

38:00.987 --> 38:02.773
Later.

38:02.989 --> 38:09.201
But when I do, I hope you'll
remember what happened today.

38:10.955 --> 38:12.946
[m1

38:13.792 --> 38:15.578
Is that it?
No.

38:15.752 --> 38:19.495
I'd like you to reach out
to Admiral Richard Abraham.

38:19.964 --> 38:23.707
He was very helpful in resolving
